om/channel/UCi06e\u2026", "expanded_url": "https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCi06ee3do1yVCinDTAway4A", "indices": [0, 23], "url": "https://t.co/075krNID5G"}]}}}, "isAutomated": false, "automatedBy": null}, "extendedEntities": {}, "card": null, "place": {}, "entities": {"hashtags": [], "symbols": [], "timestamps": [], "urls": [], "user_mentions": []}, "quoted_tweet": null, "retweeted_tweet": null, "isLimitedReply": false, "communityInfo": null, "article": null}, {"type": "tweet", "id": "2050518451354206594", "url": "https://x.com/Arronwei3n/status/2050518451354206594", "twitterUrl": "https://twitter.com/Arronwei3n/status/2050518451354206594", "text": "I like this thesis better than JPM\u2019s, which claims MediaTek is just a plan B for $AVGO.\n\n\u201cWe also believe MTK\u2019s value proposition for Google is better than the Street anticipated; MTK is the sole vendor for Google\u2019s next-gen training processor (TPU 8t), rather than just a \"low-cost SKU vendor\" serving as a backup for AVGO.\u201d\n\n_\nAletheia: In its 1Q26 earnings call, MTK raised its 2026/27E AI ASIC revenue guidance to $2bn+/$7-12bn from $1bn+/multi-billions. We were not surprised by the raise because we had already included these figures in our forecast, but the timing is 1\u20132 quarters earlier than we anticipated.\n\nMTK also guided that a second ASIC will enter HVM in 4Q27E. While the company did not specify the product, we believe it refers to the TPUv9 \"Humufish.\" MTK\u2019s management has built a reputation for guiding AI ASIC projections conservatively. As such, we believe MTK has secured sufficient supply for 2026/27E to meet its updated guidance and maintains strong control over the new technologies required for Humufish\u2014such as 300G SerDes and EMIB-T packaging\u2014or is well-prepared with backup plans.\n\nWe also believe MTK\u2019s value proposition for Google is better than the Street anticipated; MTK is the sole vendor for Google\u2019s next-gen training processor (TPU 8t), rather than just a \"low-cost SKU vendor\" serving as a backup for AVGO.", "source": "Twitter for iPhone", "retweetCount": 2, "replyCount": 1, "likeCount": 11, "quoteCount": 0, "viewCount": 1163, "createdAt": "Sat May 02 10:11:10 +0000 2026", "lang": "en", "bookmarkCount": 7, "isReply": false, "inReplyToId": null, "conversationId": "2050518451354206594", "displayTextRange": [0, 272], "inReplyToUserId": null, "inReplyToUsername": null, "author": {"type": "user", "userName": "Arronwei3n", "url": "https://x.com/Arronwei3n", "twitterUrl": "https://twitter.com/Arronwei3n", "id": "1891302848862023680", "name": "Aaron", "isVerified": false, "isBlueVerified": true, "verifiedType": null, "profilePicture": "https://pbs.twimg.com/profile_images/2007782503030075392/tzlV720X_normal.jpg", "coverPicture": "https://pbs.twimg.com/profile_banners/1891302848862023680/1764750833", "description": "", "location": "Taipei City, Taiwan", "followers": 6875, "following": 277, "status": "", "canDm": true, "canMediaTag": true, "createdAt": "Mon Feb 17 01:45:22 +0000 2025", "entities": {"description": {"urls": []}, "url": {}}, "fastFollowersCount": 0, "favouritesCount": 2455, "hasCustomTimelines": true, "isTranslator": false, "mediaCount": 276, "statusesCount": 2181, "withheldInCountries": [], "affiliatesHighlightedLabel": {}, "possiblySensitive": false, "pinnedTweetIds": ["2042063578765906343"], "profile_bio": {"description": "Semiconductor Analyst | Investor Based in Taiwan.", "entities": {"description": {}}}, "isAutomated": false, "automatedBy": null}, "extendedEntities": {}, "card": null, "place": {}, "entities": {"hashtags": [], "symbols": [{"indices": [81, 86], "text": "AVGO"}], "urls": [], "user_mentions": []}, "quoted_tweet": {"type": "tweet", "id": "2050107212283220411", "url": "https://x.com/Arronwei3n/status/2050107212283220411", "twitterUrl": "https://twitter.com/Arronwei3n/status/2050107212283220411", "text": "Mediatek TP5000, 90% upside.\n\n_\nGS: We see substantial earnings upside potential into 2028E for MediaTek underpinned by the next-generation AI ASIC projects. We now expect the ASP for the next project to be multiple times higher versus the current generation, as we see opportunity for it to engage in the compute dies design process in addition to I/O dies.\n\nWhat's more, given the higher content value to the next project, we expect the project to be GM-accretive, providing further profitability upside into 2028E. With this, we now model MediaTek\u2019s AI ASIC revenue to reach US$48bn (vs. US$19bn previously) in 2028E, accounting for 66% of its total revenue.\n\nWhile we note some investor concern around the second approach of advanced packaging technology, management addressed the concern and stated they see strong merit in the solution, with execution progressing well.", "source": "Twitter for iPhone", "retweetCount": 19, "replyCount": 8, "likeCount": 110, "quoteCount": 6, "viewCount": 46572, "createdAt": "Fri May 01 06:57:03 +0000 2026", "lang": "en", "bookmarkCount": 75, "isReply": false, "inReplyToId": null, "conversationId": "2050107212283220411", "displayTextRange": [0, 269], "inReplyToUserId": null, "inReplyToUsername": null, "author": {"type": "user", "userName": "Arronwei3n", "url": "https://x.com/Arronwei3n", "twitterUrl": "https://twitter.com/Arronwei3n", "id": "1891302848862023680", "name": "Aaron", "isVerified": false, "isBlueVerified": true, "verifiedType": null, "profilePicture": "https://pbs.twimg.com/profile_images/2007782503030075392/tzlV720X_normal.jpg", "coverPicture": "https://pbs.twimg.com/profile_banners/1891302848862023680/1764750833", "description": "", "location": "Taipei City, Taiwan", "followers": 6875, "following": 277, "status": "", "canDm": true, "canMediaTag": true, "createdAt": "Mon Feb 17 01:45:22 +0000 2025", "entities": {"description": {"urls": []}, "url": {}}, "fastFollowersCount": 0, "favouritesCount": 2455, "hasCustomTimelines": true, "isTranslator": false, "mediaCount": 276, "statusesCount